{
  "text": "Isolate Typing E. coli, K. pneumoniae, K. oxytoca and Enterobacter spp. isolates were typed using DiversiLab (bioMérieux, Marcy l'Etoile, France) [CITATION_1] . Representative E. coli isolates from dominant patterns identified by Diversilab were also analyzed by multi-locus sequence typing (MLST) (http://mlst.ucc.ie/mlst/dbs/Ecoli). Discriminatory index calculations were preformed using Ridom EpiCompare as previously described. [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "21059550",
    "[CITATION_2]": "21059550"
